project name: Optical Character Recognition
Team member 1: Anirudh V
Team Member 2: Vinod Reddy K

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HOW TO COMPILE

Type make when you are in the subdirectory where code is present
$ make

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HOW TO TRAIN

type 
$ ./train trainfile.txt < input.txt

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HOW TO RECOGNIZE 

type
$ ./recog [testimage]

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INPUT FILES

1. input.txt : This file contains the characters present in the training images.
2. trainfile.txt : This file contains the number of training images in the first line and names of the training images in subsequent lines

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TEST IMAGES (Source of all images: Google Images)

1. anumbers.png
2. number.png
3. numbers.png
4. snumber.png
5. mixed.jpg
6. alphabets2.jpg
7. handwritten.png
8. alphabets.png
9. ocr.png
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FILES USED TO STORE FEATURE VECTORS AND LABELS

1. vectors.txt : This file contains the feature vectors of all the training images.
2. labels.txt : This file contains the labels of all the training images.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TRAINING IMAGES THAT WE TRAINED UPON

1. all.png
2. all2.png
3. all3.png

A total of 1086 characters. We disregard capitals and train capitals also as small letters.